【時報-台北電】鐵道局年度大案高鐵新竹站專一區70年地上權招商結果出爐，由宏匯、環球購物中心共同組成的宏匯企業聯盟拿下最優申請人，預計明年初簽約，預估將投入155億元，打造成辦公大樓及商場。此案招商熱度更甚鄰近的新竹專二區一案，總共有三家業者投標，另外兩間為豐邑及國泰人壽。
 高鐵新竹車站專一案成功招商，意味著今年以來三大高鐵車站招商案，統統「全壘打」，同時也是宏匯公司首度跨出雙北市以外的大型複合式開發案、也是首度取得地上權土地，對「軌道經濟」投資效益相當看好。  宏匯、環球購物中心將分別以80％、20％的出資比例，共組特許公司。本案招商土地面積約1.5萬坪，最大總樓地板面積達3.24萬坪，為70年的地上權開發案，預計將規劃車站型智能商場、辦公室等使用，並以未來之心Gateway Plaza為開發定位塑造門戶新地標。  鐵道局表示，宏匯企業聯盟預計將投入155億元，並將取得鑽石級綠建築標章、黃金級LEED認證及黃金級智慧建築標章，全案規劃第一期開發於2027年完工，第二期於2029年完工啟用，將可完善站區機能，滿足地方需求並帶動高鐵站區周邊發展。  宏匯集團事業發展處總經理崔梅蘭表示，宏匯已完成台北市內湖「宏匯瑞光廣場」、新北市新莊「宏匯思源廣場」及新北市最大百貨商場「宏匯廣場」三大開發案，手中正開發的標案還有「台北雙星」、「台北車站E1E2」、「台北大學民生校區」三大案，此次得標高鐵新竹專一地上權案，也宣告宏匯首度跨出雙北市，揮軍新竹。該案也是冠德建設集團第二度與宏匯合作。  專一區招商由第一太平戴維斯擔任顧問公司，董事長黃瑞楠曾指出，新竹縣市人口成長率為全台最高，含金量也高，新竹縣可支配所得為全台第二，有穩定消費力的基礎。  另高鐵本身也可帶動人潮，疫情前高鐵新竹站每日進出站人數達3萬人，且高鐵站所在的竹北市近期發展熱絡，新竹大型開發商場多集中於此，有望帶動消費力。  鐵道局2022年多案齊發，高鐵新竹站另有專二區一案由聯發科拿下，預定投資約90億元辦理開發，並且將引進3,000個就業機會，可望帶動高鐵站區周邊發展。另外在高鐵嘉義站旁也有5公頃的事業發展用地正在公告招商，預計可引資20億元。(新聞來源 : 工商時報一李青縈、蔡惠芳／台北報導)  相關內容  台灣新生報  ·  10 小時前  交通部鐵道局辦理「高速鐵路新竹車站特定區事業發展用地開發經營案」招商 ...  風傳媒  ·  2 天前  新竹縣政府從110年起和工研院、科技之星交通、車王電子及銓鼎科技合作，推行「新竹縣高鐵自駕接駁運行實驗計畫」，...  時報資訊  ·  2 天前  【時報-台北電】新竹縣政府2021年起推行新竹縣高鐵自駕接駁運行實驗計畫，並與工業技術研究院、科技之星交通、車王電子及銓鼎科技股份有限公司合作，該計畫是全國首個在實際人車混流道路測試的計畫。首輛自駕巴士上路測試後，今年擴大測試路線，並在引進3輛電動中巴進行自駕化改造完成，同時取得掛試車牌，預計11月中正式上路測試，最晚明年底正式上路營運，目標納入市區公車營運路線。 交通旅遊處長游志祥說，高鐵自駕接駁運行實驗計畫從2021年啟動，由工研院打造第1輛實驗車上路，運行一段時間，接續計畫投入3輛車輛。科技之星交通公司30日舉辦高鐵自駕接駁運行車輛展示活動，新領牌照的3輛自駕車也同步亮相。 3輛自駕車經過經濟部審查，在今年10月獲核准延長實驗期1年，同時取得交通部試車牌，預計今年11月中上路測試。游志祥表示，計畫初期實驗路線由高鐵七路出發，經文興路、嘉豐五路、光明六路形成循環路線，今年實驗路線將再由光明六路延伸至莊敬北路AI智慧園區周邊，串連高鐵新竹站到社區、學校、百貨商場、產業園區等，在一般汽機車混合市區開放道路進行自駕測試。 自駕車第1階段先採取不載客測試，並以夜間10時至1時先行測試後，再  中華日報  ·  1 天前  記者彭新茹∕新竹報導 新竹縣政府和工業技術研究院、科技之星交通、車王電子及銓鼎科技股份有限公司合作，推行「新竹 […]  Denne geniale oppfinnelsen stopper snorking og forbedrer søvnen. 新竹 市以「風城」聞名，近日新竹市地區受 東北季風 加上奈格 颱風 外圍環流等因素影響，最強刮起9級強陣風，不少新竹人都感受強烈，還陸續傳出有路人、騎士被吹倒送醫，有網友喊説能否放「巨風假？」  新竹市政府官方粉專也接到私訊詢問「能不能放假？」市府說明，須持續偵測平均風力7級以上或陣風達10級以上，可能出現致災情況時，才會做出停班課的決定。
 新竹氣象站資訊指出，受颱風外圍環流影響及東北季風增強影響，新竹地區今天為陰短暫陣雨的天氣，空曠地區易有8至9級強陣風，也提醒民眾新竹沿海風力8至9陣風11級，浪高4至5公尺，請特別注意。  新竹市最近風勢強勁，新竹馬偕紀念醫院急診外科主任白永嘉日前就在臉書發文提醒，「新竹的風真的非常大！」有老人走路、4個年輕人騎車各自在不同地方被側風吹倒，受傷送急診，有骨折的、有脫臼的，累計10人被風吹倒送醫。  距離年底選舉20多天，不少候選人懸掛的選舉看板也被強風吹破「掛彩」，成了另類風災受災戶，或是看板帆布搖搖欲墜，恐有公安疑慮，緊急通知廠商處理；也有候選人站路口拜票也幾乎被風吹到挺不直腰，格外艱辛。  新竹市政府官方臉書粉絲專頁「新竹市 新鮮事」最新發文指出，新竹市因為東北季風加上奈格颱風外圍環流，以及西半部受海峽地形效應影響，根據觀測站數據顯示，新竹市香山區，最大陣風達23.8m/s（9級），平均陣風也有13.3m/s（6級），請大家出門，一定要注意自身安全。  至於是否能夠停班停課？市府說明，依據《天然災害停止上班及上課作業辦法》第4條規定第一「依據氣象預報，颱風暴風半徑於四小時內可能經過之地區，其平均風力可達7級以上或陣風可達10級以上。」  扣除颱風來襲外，無颱風期間，如偵測平均風力7級以上或陣風達10級以上，必須「持續」偵測到相同強度的風力，或因應地形（如山區）或雨勢影響，可能出現致災情況時，才會做出停班課的決定。  議員蔡惠婷最近分享選舉看板被風吹壞。圖／取自蔡惠婷臉書  新竹市風大，街頭常見女生長髮被風吹亂。圖／取自「新竹市 新鮮事」臉書  相關新聞  贊助廣告  商品推薦  FB留言  udn討論區  共 則留言

With the 2023 FIFA Women’s World Cup in Australia and New Zealand fast approaching, Canada head coach Bev Priestman is looking to make the most of the little time remaining to prepare her team for a title run.
The next step on the journey to the World Cup will take the Canadian women’s national soccer team to Sao Paulo, Brazil for a pair of international friendlies against the best team in South America. Canada will play Brazil on Nov. 11 and again on Nov. 15.  On Monday, Priestman announced the squad travelling to Brazil, which includes all-time leading goal scorer and newly minted NWSL champion Christine Sinclair.  Canada goes into the two matches on a four-game winning streak, having defeated Argentina and Morocco in the previous women’s international window in early October. In September, Canada won two games against Australia, in Australia.  “I think they (Brazil) are going to ask great questions of us, given some of the absences that we have and some of their strengths,” Priestman said Monday. “But at the end of the day, I think for us, what I wasn’t so happy with previously, has been our performance throughout 90 minutes.  “I think that is sometimes about depth; because when you’re missing some key players, you’re going deeper into your roster. But I’ve been incredibly impressed with those that I have put on the pitch.”  The return of Sinclair and defender Ashley Lawrence to the squad after missing the previous international window, highlights Canada’s squad selection, but Priestman will be without a number of key players in Brazil.  Janine Beckie is getting time off after a long season, which concluded with her also winning an NWSL championship with Portland, while defenders Vanessa Gilles, Allysha Chapman, and striker Deanne Rose are not available due to injury. US college players Jayde Riviere, Simi Awujo, and Zoe Burns are also not available due to school commitments.  In Brazil, Priestman will be balancing between evaluating talent and trying to find the right combinations on the filed leading towards the World Cup in July, where Canada will play Nigeria, the Republic of Ireland and co-hosts Australia in the group stage.  “If you look at the last three (international) windows, I’m not sure this team has ever had this level of depletion,” Priestman said. “In many ways it’s a blessing (looking at new players), but it’s also a curse in other ways, because the consistency and fluidity of the partnerships is naturally disrupted.  “But at the end of the day, I think the team is better off for it, because we’ve found more talent. The young players have put their best foot forward and it’s going to be a difficult job to pick 23 or what could be 26 players, going into that World Cup.”  Canada is heading into the World Cup as defending Olympic champions. Canada is expected to get out of its group and challenge for the title. The upcoming tournament was expanded to 32 teams from 24 in 2019 where Canada made it to the second round before being eliminated by Sweden.  Canada’s best performance at a Women’s World Cup was in 2003 when it made it to the semifinal of the tournament in the United States and eventually finished fourth.  While Canada has played well in its last few exhibition matches, despite missing some key players, Priestman is still looking for more out of the club heading towards Australia and New Zealand.  “We’ve defended very well, clean sheets (shutouts) are a big part of what we are,” Priestman said. “We are also scoring goals and we are doing that from different positions and different areas. I think being able to do that against top team like Brazil, who don’t concede a lot of goals, that will be a big thing for us to push towards.  “I’d love to get a six-game winning streak towards the back end of 2022, which has been a great year for us, and the confidence that gives you going into a World Cup year. I think we need to work on that consistency for 90 minutes. We can start games stronger, which was a problem in some other series, or end games stronger, for sure.”  Priestman will have two more international windows, in February and April, prior to the World Cup, which runs from July 20 to Aug. 20. She will have to select her final World Cup roster following the April international window.  “We’re in the final stages of setting up February, which we hope will be a tournament setting, which we were in previously (Arnold Clark Cup),” Priestman said. “Then in April, we’re currently trying to secure a home game if we can. We’ll prioritize in trying to get the best opponent, but we’re hoping in can be in Canada. Then in June we’ll have some preparation games in Australia.  “There is not a lot of time and not a lot of games, but I’m pleased to say February is secured, and so we’re just working on some final details of that.”  CANADA  GK – Sabrina D’Angelo | SWE / Vittsjö GIK  GK – Lysianne Proulx | POR / SCU Torreense  GK – Kailen Sheridan | USA / San Diego Wave FC  CB – Kadeisha Buchanan | ENG / Chelsea FC  CB – Shelina Zadorsky | ENG / Tottenham Hotspur  FB – Gabrielle Carle | SWE / Kristianstads DFF  FB – Ashley Lawrence | FRA / Paris Saint-Germain  FB – Bianca St-Georges | USA / Chicago Red Stars  FB – Ella Ottey | CAN / NDC-CDN Ontario  FB – Marie Levasseur | FRA / Fleury FC  FB/CB – Sura Yekka | FRA / Le Havre AC  M – Jessie Fleming | ENG / Chelsea FC  M – Julia Grosso | ITA / Juventus FC  M – Quinn | USA / OL Reign  M – Sophie Schmidt | USA / Houston Dash  M – Desiree Scott | USA / Kansas City Current  M – Christine Sinclair | USA / Portland Thorns FC  F – Amanda Allen | CAN / NDC-CDN Ontario  F – Annabelle Chukwu | CAN / NDC-CDN Ontario  F – Jordyn Huitema | USA / OL Reign  F – Cloé Lacasse | POR / SL Benfica  F – Clarissa Larisey | SCO / Glasgow Celtic FC  F – Adriana Leon | ENG / Manchester United FC  F – Nichelle Prince | USA / Houston Dash  F – Evelyne Viens | SWE / Kristianstads DFF
